<p>The <b>M4 Carbine</b> is a family of firearms tracing its lineage back to earlier <a href="/wiki/Carbine" title="Carbine">carbine</a> versions of the <a href="/wiki/M16_rifle" title="M16 rifle">M16</a>, all based on the original <a href="/wiki/AR-15" title="AR-15">AR-15</a> made by <a href="/wiki/ArmaLite" title="ArmaLite">ArmaLite</a>. It is a shorter and lighter version of the <a href="/wiki/M16_rifle#M16A2" title="M16 rifle">M16A2</a> <a href="/wiki/Assault_rifle" title="Assault rifle">assault rifle</a>, achieving 80% parts commonality with the M16A2.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> The <b>M4</b> has <a href="/wiki/Selective_fire" title="Selective fire">selective fire</a> options including <a href="/wiki/Semi-automatic_firearm" title="Semi-automatic firearm">semi-automatic</a> and <a href="/wiki/Burst_mode_(firearm)" title="Burst mode (firearm)">three-round burst</a> (like the M16A2), while the <b>M4A1</b> has a "<a href="/wiki/Automatic_firearm" title="Automatic firearm">full auto</a>" option in place of the three-round burst.</p>
